            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Cut 2 pieces of<strong> tin foil</strong> approx. the size of A4 paper</p><p>Lay the <strong>onion wedges</strong> in the middle of the 2 pieces of foil, (doubling it up prevents any leakages!) and top with your <strong>dried bay leaf[ves]</strong> and the <strong>browned pork</strong> (skin-side up)</p><p>Loosely scrunch the edges of the foil around the pork leaving the skin exposed and transfer the parcel[s] to a baking tray</p>",
      "order": 4,
      "media": {
        "images": [
