    {
      "instruction": "<p>Combine 50ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[75ml]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[100ml]</span> <strong>boiled water </strong>with the<strong> pineapple juice</strong>,<strong> soy sauce</strong>,<strong> red wine vinegar</strong>,<strong> </strong>1 tsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[1 1/2 tsp]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[2 tsp]</span><strong> sugar </strong>and a pinch of <strong>salt </strong>– this is your <strong>stock</strong></p><p>Pour the <strong>stock </strong>around the pork</p><p>Put the tray in the oven for 1 hour or until the pork skin is crisp and the meat is cooked through and tender (no pink meat!) – this is your <strong>Filipino-style pork belly</strong></p>",
