    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once the pork has had 45 min, add the<strong> sliced garlic</strong> with a drizzle of <strong>olive oil</strong> to a medium pot with a lid and fry for 1-2 min or until fragrant</p><p>Add your <strong>white long grain rice</strong> with 225ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[300ml] </span><span class=\"text-danger\">[450ml]</span> <strong>cold water</strong> and bring to the boil over a high heat then reduce the heat to very low and cook, covered, for 12-15 min or until all the water has absorbed</p><p>Once cooked through remove from the heat and set aside (lid on) to steam until serving – this is your <strong>garlic rice</strong></p>",
